<center><table border=0><tr><td><center><H2><font face=arial>The Disciples of Shadow Return!</font></H2></center>
<font face=arial size=2><b>Posted By:</b> <A HREF="/cgi-local/whois.cgi?Lord Damas">Lord Damas</a><br>
<b>Posted On:</b> 8:40 p.m. 11/4/1999<br>
<b>Subject:</b> The Disciples of Shadow Return!<p>
<br><center><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/datel.gif" width=46 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dateblnk.gif" width=100 height=22 border=0><img src="http://www.everworld.net/images/dater.gif" width=306 height=22 border=0></center><BR></STRONG><FONT SIZE=2 color=#F4D99F FACE=arial>
<P>#1. Is the Disciples of Shadow an evil guild?

<P>No, the Disciples are not evil per se. But we will resort to tactics that some blind servants of Light consider brutal or underhanded, as per the Dark Virtues of Cunning and Strength, to reach our goals.
<P>#2. Are there racial and/or class requirements to joining to the Disciples?
<P>No, all races and classes are welcome in the ranks of the Disciples. The Darkness harbors no such prejudices.
<P>#3. Are the Disciples a PK guild?
<P>No. Characters of either type have a place within the guild. Random and rampant banditry will not be tolerated by the current Shadowlord.
<P>#4. Do the Disciples have any enemies simply because of their ideals and practices?
<P>Not to our knowledge. There may be other guilds or players who harbor such resentment, but if so it has not been drawn to our attention.
<P>#5. Are the Disciples currently allied with any other guilds, clans, or orders?
<P>The Disciples of Shadow are the founding guild of the Shadow Coalition. We have a mutual defense pact with all other Coalition members as per the Coalition Charter. However though, we haven't had contact with the other Coalition guilds for some time. It will be delt with later, pending the reconstruction of DoS.
<P>#6. What server will the Disciples be playing on?
<P>The Disciples shall be placed on The Rathe Server. All members are required to have a character on Rathe. After we get 9 members back, I shall register the guild with EQ.
<P>#7. What happened to the Disciples before that now the guild has to be reformed?
<P>A very long story. To shorten it up, we lost our leadership. Our Second Shadowlord, Ix, was not paying any attention to DoS. We soon then began to crumble and fall apart. Ix disappeared without a warning nor reason. This is why we reformed under new leadership.
<P>I posted the FAQs of our guild to answer questions up front. We are a very deticated guild, and are reforming. Join us in our darkness at http://freeweb.digiweb.com/games/damas7/DoS.html
<P>Until next time, let darness prevail...
<P>-Lord Damas
<BR>
</FONT></td></tr></table></P>
